  "prompt": "What is the salary of an assistant in CSS after 7th pay commission?",
  "response": "As of the 7th Pay Commission implementation in India, the salary of an Assistant in the Central Secretariat Service (CSS) is determined by the pay matrix.\n\nFor an Assistant in CSS, the pay scale is typically at Level 6 of the Pay Matrix. The basic pay at Level 6 ranges from approximately \u20b935,400 to \u20b91,12,400, depending on years of experience and seniority. \n\nIn addition to the basic salary, there are various allowances such as Dearness Allowance (DA), House Rent Allowance (HRA), and other benefits that can significantly increase the total salary. The DA is revised periodically and is a percentage of the basic pay.\n\nTo get the most accurate and current information, it\u2019s best to consult official government sources or any recent notifications related to salary structures.",
